Midwest Energy Emissions Corp.


                  Midwest Energy Emissions Corp. is an environmental services company, which specializes in mercury emission control technologies, primarily to utility and industrial coal-fired units. It develops and delivers mercury capture systems and technologies to power plants and industrial coal-fired units. The company was founded by Richard A. MacPherson on July 19, 1983 and is headquartered in Lewis Center, OH.                




